data.post:
Our russian guests from Creative Grasp has left Denmark again, bringing a lot of inspiration from Aarhus and Odense: 
Ellen Riis and her student Johanne gave us a great insight  into the entrepreneurial learning as part of the film Education Multiplatform Storytelling and Production. Nick Jary introduced us to the action learning part of the Kaospilot Study. Aarhus Street Food opened  the doors  for meals and an interesting talk with Nikolaj Kirk from Hjerl Hede Open Air Museum. We continued to the craft community at Jaegergaardsgade 152, where we were introduced  by Lisbeth Solsoe, Julie Back, Ann Hoejgaard Slot from Heimkaer and Astrid Skibsted Holm. At night we went to Godsbanen. Friday we attended entrepreneuriel training at the Music Academy in Odense with our Star, Cecilia Krill. No wonder, if the hearts and minds are full. We will meet again in Arkhangelsk in December, and have created a lot of new and valuable connections in Denmark.
